HJR26 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 RECOGNIZING AND COMMENDING MCKENZIE FULLER FOR OUTSTANDING
4 ACHIEVEMENT AND SERVICE AS MISS JACKSONVILLE STATE
5 UNIVERSITY 2025.
6
7 WHEREAS, on January 24, 2025, McKenzie Fuller was
8 crowned Miss Jacksonville State University, earning the
9 honor to serve as a distinguished ambassador for
10 Jacksonville State University and its student body; and
11 WHEREAS, she proudly hails from Ohatchee, Alabama,
12 and exemplifies the values of her community through
13 leadership, integrity, and commitment to service; and
14 WHEREAS, Ms. Fuller has championed her Community
15 Service Initiative, Reading Rockets: The Importance of
16 Childhood Literacy, encouraging early reading habits and
17 promoting literacy development among children across
18 Alabama; and
19 WHEREAS, through her literacy advocacy, she has
20 conducted a statewide book drive that successfully collected
21 2,500 books for children and families in need, thereby
22 increasing access to reading materials and supporting
23 literacy development; and
24 WHEREAS, she has further strengthened early learning
25 by visiting 43 classrooms, directly engaging hundreds of
26 students in reading activities and literacy enrichment; and
27 WHEREAS, demonstrating her commitment to empowering
28 young women in education and innovation, she created and
Page 1

young women in education and innovation, she created and
HJR26 Enrolled
29 hosted a Girls in STEAM event, promoting female
30 participation and confidence in science, technology,
31 engineering, arts, and mathematics fields; and
32 WHEREAS, she has worked to empower young learners and
33 support educational equity, understanding that strong
34 literacy foundations are critical to lifelong academic
35 success and community advancement; and
36 WHEREAS, Ms. Fuller has represented Jacksonville
37 State University with distinction at official engagements,
38 campus programs, and community events, embodying the spirit
39 of scholarship, service, success, and style; and
40 WHEREAS, she proudly represented Jacksonville State
41 University at the Miss Alabama Competition, continuing to
42 elevate the importance of literacy, education, and community
43 service throughout the State of Alabama; now therefore,
44 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
45 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That McKenzie Fuller is hereby
46 recognized and commended for her exemplary leadership,
47 academic excellence, and dedicated service to literacy,
48 education, and youth empowerment.
49 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
50 resolution be presented to Ms. Fuller in appreciation of her
51 accomplishments and with best wishes for continued success
52 in all her future endeavors.
